cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.CG, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with online routing algorithms on geometric graphs, specifically the $\Theta$6-graph and the half-$\Theta$6-graph, which are commonly studied in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves analyzing the routing performance on graphs defined on a Poisson point process, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the geometric properties of the graphs, which is relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves analyzing the expected routing ratio, which is a measure of information theory, and thus falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes memoryless and constant-memory routing algorithms, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
